FOOT & MOUTH DISEASE, CATTLE - MONGOLIA
****************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
[1]
Date: 5 May 2000
From: Jacques H. Jeugmans<jjeugmans@adb.org>
Source: Mongolia daily news No.088 (909), 4 May 2000 [edited]

Miscellaneous Quarantine regarding Foot and Mouth Disease (FMD)
---------------------------------------------------------------
The Minister of Agriculture and Industry Ch. Sodnomtseren briefed the
Cabinet members on present conditions of the quarantine in Dornogovi aimag.
About MNT14 million is required to purchase necessary disinfecting ingredients.
The State Emergency Commission has convened a meeting. As the Vice-Chairman
of the Commission, the Minister of Environment S. Mendsaihan, informed the
newspaper, Udriin Sonin, the disease was caused by a virus [from?] Taiwan,
according to the first test results sent from Moscow. As of 8 p.m. 3 May
2000, of 523 infected animals, 77 died, there are 18 households in
Ulaanbadrah soum with infected animals. The Ministry of Health and Social
Welfare is organizing health protection actions and food supply of the
population in the area.
The Government will compensate [for] the loss of dead and infected animals.
Besides 5 people, including a lawmaker, were revealed to come by train from
the quarantine site, and they are under the clinical control. The
administrations of Dornogovi aimag and Monitoring Department of the
Ministry of Agriculture and Industry have done nothing despite the reports
of the disease outbreak in China and Korea.
The Director of the center of Fighting the Natural Infectious Disease J.
Batbold made a report yesterday, in which he emphasized the internationally
recognized disease of *A* category [status] can be eradicated only by
following strict emergency regulations and special instructions of work there.
Meat and milk exports from the area shall be prohibited for one year. Since
1974, there has been no report of foot and mouth disease in Mongolia.
--
Jacques H. Jeugmans
<jjeugmans@adb.org>
[Human cases of Foot and Mouth Disease are extremely rare. They are NOT
life threatening and are mild enough that most people do not miss work. It
is quite sad these people are quarantined. - Mod. TG]
***
[2]
Date: 4 May 2000
From: jjeugmans@adb.org
Source: Mongolia daily news No.087 (908), 5 May 2000 [edited]

Quarantine Imposed In Dornogovi
--------------------------------
In connection with the outbreak of a dangerous infectious disease of
animals in some soums of Dornogovi aimag, the Cabinet called an emergency
meeting and on the basis of the relevant laws and regulations decided to
take declare a special quarantine for whole territories of Ulaanbadrah,
Erdene, Huvsgul, Sainshand, Zamyn-Uud soums, and other territories of the
province under a limited quarantine, and declared an alert, as Udriin Sonin
(a Mongolian newspaper) reports.
During the emergency situation, the Governor of Dornogovi aimag was
instructed to take measures for regulating and banning traffic of people,
transport means and movement of livestock. According to the report received
by the State Civil Defense Board, 435 animals have been infected with this
foot-and-mouth disease (FMD), out of which 61 cows, 2 sheep, a goat and a
camel have died.
In the affected localities, people were mobilized to liquidate the carrions
of dead animals. The State Service of Veterinary Control and the State
Emergency Commission yesterday dispatched experts to Dornogovi to collect
probes from the dead animals. The probes will be sent to the Moscow.
--
Jacques H. Jeugmans
<jjeugmans@adb.org>
